Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Neurovascular Thrombectomy Devices Market

The neurovascular thrombectomy devices market is expected to witness market growth at a rate of 6.60% in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. Data Bridge Market Research report on neurovascular thrombectomy devices market provides analysis and insights regarding the various factors expected to be prevalent throughout the forecast period while providing their impacts on the marketâ€™s growth. The rapid advancements in the healthcare sector globally is escalating the growth of neurovascular thrombectomy devices market.

Thrombectomy refers to a surgical procedure for removing the blood clots formed in the blood vessel of the brain. Neurovascular thrombectomy devices, also called cerebral thrombectomy devices that are widely utilized for retrieving or destroying blood clots in the cerebral region.

The increase in the relevance of ischemic stroke across the globe acts as one of the major factors driving the growth of neurovascular thrombectomy devices market. The high focus on the procedure owning to the availability of a large pool of clinical data demonstrating the efficacy of mechanical thrombectomy devices, and favorable reimbursement scenario accelerate the market growth. The rise in initiatives taken by the government and non-profit organizations to spread awareness regarding ischemic stokes and their preventive measures, and increase in demand for minimally invasive neurosurgical procedures further influence the market. Additionally, increase in number of hospitals, rise in population, impressive reimbursement policies and expansion of healthcare infrastructure positively affects the neurovascular thrombectomy devices market. Furthermore, product launches and commercialization, and increase in the number of research activities in the field of neurovascular therapies extend profitable opportunity to the market players in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

On the other hand, high procedural cost and presence of stringent regulations are expected to obstruct the market growth. The limited patient awareness related to thrombectomy and lack of trained healthcare professionals are projected to challenge the neurovascular thrombectomy devices market in the forecast period of 2021-2028.

